==English==
===Etymology===
{{L.}} ''[[subitus]]'', "sudden", from the feeling of immediately knowing the number of items present

===Verb===
{{wikipediapar|subitizing and counting}}
{{en-infl-reg-other-e|subitiz|e}}

#{{transitive}} to [[judge]] (the [[number]] of [[object]]s in a [[group]]) [[rapidly]], [[accurately]] and [[confidently]] without [[count]]ing them
#{{intransitive}} to have the ability of judging the number of objects in a group in this way

====Forms and variants====
*[[subitise]] (''mainly UK'')

